result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin O Davison was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dustin O Davison is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dustin O Davison was found guilty of Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install [Modifiers: Extend Order for Ignition Interlock Device], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: from Clerk to Defendant re: Court-ordered Payment Arrangements

9:34 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - met with the District Attorney and will accept the offer.  DA recites offer, upon plea to count 2, will recommend a fine and costs, and extension of the IID and the balance of the counts will be dismissed.  Defendant concurs.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 2 as charged.  Court orders the balance of the counts be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-$150 fine plus court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-Extension of IID - 6 months
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court adjourned at 9:41 a.m.

9:23 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by the defendant - in the process of getting the money to retain one.  Court sets for Status Hearing on November 24, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  Defendant to make an appointment with the District Attorney.

Court adjourned at 9:26 a.m.

9:38 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - requests a little more time.  Court sets for Status Hearing on October 27, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:39 a.m.

9:39 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - will be getting an attorney, retaining one privately.  Court will set for statusd hearing on September 22, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:40 a.m.

9:21 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Defendant stands mute.  Court enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behalf of the defendant.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond.  Court will set for Status Hearing on August 25, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:23 a.m.
